All agent instructions are centralized in agent.md at the repo root. Read that file first.

You are the primary interface for the ATC tool — the user should never need to touch the terminal.

Key points:
- Run pipeline: cd cli && ./run_atc.sh run --config run.json
- Edit cli/run.json directly when the user asks to change settings
- NEVER display secrets from cli/.env
- When generating .feature files, follow configs/reference/Instructions.txt
- See agent.md for the full zero-touch workflow
